 11 -----------
  
 12 Recipe·code·wraps·at·79·characters·and·passes·flake8.·Strings·should·single

 14 100%·code·coverage.
  
13 ------------------ 
14 Creating·a·Shelf 
15 ------------------ 
  
  
16 A·:class:`Shelf·<recipe.Shelf>`·is·a·place·to·store·SQL·fragments.·In·recipe 
17 these·are·called·:class:`Ingredients·<recipe.Ingredient>`.·Ingredients·can 
18 contain·columns·that·should·be·part·of·the·``SELECT``·portion·of·a·query, 
19 filters·that·are·part·of·the·``WHERE``·clause·of·a·query,·group_bys·that 
20 contribute·to·a·query's·``GROUP·BY``·and·havings·which·add·``HAVING``·limits 
21 ot·a·query. 
  
22 It's·a·safe·bet·that·you·won't·have·to·construct·an·Ingredient 
23 with·all·these·parts·directly·because·Recipe·contains·convenience·classes 
24 that·help·you·build·the·most·common·SQL·fragments.·The·two·most·common 
25 Ingredient·subclasses·are·:class:`Dimensions·<recipe.Dimension>`·which·supply 
26 both·a·column·and·a·grouping·on·that·column·and 
27 :class:`Metrics·<recipe.Metric>`·which·supply·a·column·aggregation. 
  
28 Shelf·acts·like·a·dictionary.·The·keys·are·strings·and·the 
29 values·are·Ingredients.·The·keys·are·a·shortcut·name·for·the 
30 ingredient.·Here's·an·example. 
  
31 :: 
  
32 ····from·recipe·import·* 
  
33 ····shelf·=·Shelf({ 
34 ········'age':·WtdAvgMetric(Census.age,·Census.pop2000), 
35 ········'population':·Metric(func.sum(Census.pop2000)), 
36 ········'state',·Dimension(Census.state) 
37 ····}) 
  
38 This·is·a·shelf·with·two·metrics·(a·weighted·average·of·age,·and·the·sum·of 
39 population)·and·a·dimension·which·lets·you·group·on·US·State·names. 
  
  
40 --------------------------------- 
41 Using·the·Shelf·to·build·a·Recipe 
42 --------------------------------- 
  
43 Now·that·you·have·the·shelf,·you·can·build·a·recipe 
  
44 Quick·example·of·a·recipe15 ..·_scm:
  
45 Basic·parts·of·a·recipe16 --------------

 36 ******·Recipe:·A·tool·for·building·reusable·SQLÂ¶·******
 37 Release·v0.8.0.·(Installation)
 38 Recipe·is·an·MIT·licensed·cross-database·querying·library,·written·in·Python.
 39 It·allows·you·to·reuse·SQL·fragments·to·answer·data·questions·consistently.
 40 Extension·classes·allow·you·to·support·data·anonymization,·automatic·generation
 41 of·where·clauses,·user·permissioning·to·data,·subselects,·and·response
 42 formatting.
 43 >>>·shelf·=·Shelf({
 44 ···'age':·WtdAvgMetric(Census.age,·Census.pop2000),
 45 ···'state':·Dimension(Census.state)
 46 })
 47 >>>·recipe·=·Recipe().shelf(shelf=shelf)\
 48 ····.metrics('age')\
 49 ····.dimensions('state')\
 50 ····.order_by('-age')
  
 51 >>>·recipe.to_sql()
 52 SELECT·census.state·AS·state,
 53 ·······CAST(sum(census.age·*·census.pop2000)·AS·FLOAT)·/·(coalesce(CAST(sum
 54 (census.pop2000)·AS·FLOAT),·0.0)·+·1e-09)·AS·age
 55 FROM·census
 56 GROUP·BY·census.state
 57 ORDER·BY·CAST(sum(census.age·*·census.pop2000)·AS·FLOAT)·/·(coalesce(CAST(sum
 58 (census.pop2000)·AS·FLOAT),·0.0)·+·1e-09)·DESC
  
 59 >>>·recipe.dataset.csv
 60 state,age,state_id
 61 Florida,39.08283934000634,Florida
 62 West·Virginia,38.555058651148165,West·Virginia
 63 Maine,38.10118393261269,Maine
 64 Pennsylvania,38.03856695544053,Pennsylvania
